verbs.description: vacuate (third-person singular simple present vacuates, present participle vacuating, simple past and past participle vacuated)

examples: Mr. Toynbee recommends, in cases of ruptured membrane tympani, "directing the stream of water [in syringing] through the orifice of the membrane into the tympanum in order to vacuate the latter cavity of its contents."
